{"title_page": "BYD Company", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{for|its automaker subsidiary|BYD Auto}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = BYD Co Ltd <br /> \u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\n| logo = BuildYourDreams.svg\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{hkse|1211}}<br>{{szse|002594}}\n| genre = \n| foundation = {{start date and age|1995|2|df=yes}}\n| founder = [[Wang Chuanfu]]\n| location_city = [[Shenzhen]], [[Guangdong]]\n| location_country = China\n| location = \n| origins = \n| key_people = Wang Chuanfu ([[Chairman]], [[CEO]])\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| industry = [[Automobiles]], [[Buses]], [[Electric bicycle]], [[Truck]], [[Forklift]], [[Solar Panels]], [[Rechargeable batteries]]\n| products = Gasoline and electric cars, battery-powered bicycles, buses, truck, forklift, photovoltaic modules (solar panels), rechargeable batteries and handset components.\n| services = \n| revenue = US$8.5&nbsp;billion (2013)\n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| num_employees = 220,000 in 2017<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = [[BYD Automobile]]<br>[[BYD Electronic]]\n| owner = {{unbulleted list\n | [[Berkshire Hathaway]]<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-03-09|title=Why China's War on Pollution Affects the Whole World|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/graphics/2018-china-pollution/|newspaper=Bloomberg.com|via=www.bloomberg.com|quote=Beneficiaries include BYD Co., a Warren Buffett-backed carmaker that soared 67 percent last year and sold more cars than Tesla.}}</ref> (24.6%)<ref name=\"4-traders\">{{cite web|title=BYD Company|url=http://www.4-traders.com/BYD-COMPANY-LIMITED-5640763/company/|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref>\n | Xiang Yang L\u00fc (21.6%)<ref name=\"4-traders\"/>\n | [[Wang Chuanfu]] (15.7%)<ref name=\"4-traders\"/>\n}}\n| homepage = [http://www.byd.com www.byd.com]\n}}\n\n{{Chinese|s=\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8|t=|p=B\u01d0y\u00e0d\u00ed G\u01d4f\u0113n Y\u01d2uxi\u00e0n G\u014dngs\u012b|order=st}}\n'''BYD Co Ltd''' is a Chinese manufacturer of automobiles, battery-powered bicycles, buses, forklifts, solar panels, rechargeable batteries (varied inc. bulk-storage from renewable energy), trucks, etc.<ref name=\"BYD2\">[http://www.bydit.com/doce/about/company_p.asp Company Profile] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090427135652/http://www.bydit.com/doce/about/company_p.asp |date=27 April 2009 }} BYD Official Site</ref> with its corporate headquarters in [[Shenzhen]]. It has two major subsidiaries, [[BYD Automobile]] and [[BYD Electronic]]. It was founded in February 1995.\n\nBYD has grown to become a major manufacturer of automobiles, battery-powered bicycles, buses, truck, forklift, solar panels, rechargeable batteries, and most notably mobile-phone batteries.<ref name=gunther/>\n\nBYD topped the 2010 [[Bloomberg Businessweek]] Tech 100 list, a list of large, fast-growing tech companies.<ref name=businessweek2>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/it100_2010.html?chan=technology_special+report+--+tech+100_special+report+--+tech+100 |title=The Tech 100 |magazine=[[BusinessWeek]] |accessdate=26 May 2010 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100524080821/http://www.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/it100_2010.html?chan=technology_special+report+--+tech+100_special+report+--+tech+100| archivedate= 24 May 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n==Name==\nThe name BYD is an abbreviation of \"Build Your Dreams\".<ref name=\"NYT\">[https://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/13/business/worldbusiness/13chinacar.html?_r=1&ref=business A Small Showing, but With Big Dreams] NICK BUNKLEY\nPublished: 12 January 2009</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Byd us headquarter la.JPG|thumb|BYD US Headquarters in Los Angeles]]\nFounded in February 1995<ref name=\"BYD2\"/> and listed on the [[Hong Kong Stock Exchange]] on 31 July<ref name=\"BYD Auto About\">[http://www.byd.com/company.php?index=0 Company Profile] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090826100551/http://www.byd.com/company.php?index=0 |date=26 August 2009 }} BYD Auto Official Site</ref> 2002,<ref name=\"BYD1\">[http://www.byd.com.cn/Welcome to BYD]{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Company Introduction, BYD Official Site</ref> BYD Co Ltd began as a rechargeable-battery factory competing in the Chinese market against Japanese imports.<ref name=gunther/>\n\n===Early growth===\nBYD grew quickly within ten years capturing more than half the world's mobile-phone battery market<ref name=\"Book\"/> and becoming the largest Chinese manufacturer (and in the top four worldwide) of all types of [[rechargeable battery|rechargeable batteries]].<ref name=gunther>{{cite magazine|url=http://money.cnn.com/2009/04/13/technology/gunther_electric.fortune/ |title=Why Warren Buffett is investing in electric car company BYD |author=Marc Gunther |magazine=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] |date=13 April 2009 |accessdate=2 May 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090427114106/http://money.cnn.com/2009/04/13/technology/gunther_electric.fortune/ |archivedate=27 April 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Replacing work done by machines with cheap, local labor lowered costs,<ref name=\"Book\">[https://books.google.com/books?id=aKfmQdqvk0wC&pg=PA215&dq=BYD&client=safari#v=onepage&q=BYD&f=false China, Inc. By Ted Fishman] Google Books, page 215</ref> and the company began expanding beyond batteries adding automobiles and mobile phone components.\n\n===Automobiles===\n{{main|BYD Automobile}}\nA year after the 2002 acquisition of Tsinchuan Automobile Co Ltd, [[BYD Auto|BYD Automobile Co Ltd]] was born.<ref name=\"BYD Auto About\"/> One of many Chinese automakers, in 2010 it was the sixth largest in terms of sales volume.<ref>[http://www.thetruthaboutcars.com/2011/01/china-car-market-101-who-makes-all-those-18-million-cars/ China Car Market 101: Who Makes All Those 18 Million Cars?] thetruthaboutcars.com, 19 January 2011</ref>\n\nSeeking to utilize BYD battery production resources, it sells electric cars in addition to gasoline-powered models.\n\nIn late 2017, the premier of the government of [[Ontario]], Canada announced that BYD would open a factory in the province to manufacture electric vehicles. Other sources indicated that the plant could open as early as 2018.<ref> {{Cite web|url=https://canada.businesschief.com/marketing/2202/Chinas-BYD-to-open-electric-vehicle-plant-in-Ontario|title=China\u2019s BYD to open electric vehicle plant in Ontario|website=canada.businesschief.com|access-date=2019-05-31}}</ref> BYD already had a small Canadian office in Windsor, Ontario at the time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/queenspark/2017/12/01/chinese-truck-manufacturer-to-open-ontario-factory-premier-says-on-trade-trip.html|title=Chinese truck manufacturer to open Ontario factory, Premier says on trade trip {{!}} The Star|website=thestar.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Monorail Transit ===\nIn 2016, BYD unveiled a working monorail prototype known as \"Skyrail\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.byd.com/skyrail/|title=SKYRAIL|website=BYD USA|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.byd.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/SkyRail%20Brochure.pdf|title=BYD SkyRail|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> and announced they will enter the global rail transit market.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cleantechnica.com/2016/10/14/byd-unveils-skyrail-test-track-shenzhen-china/|title=BYD Unveils SkyRail Test Track In Shenzhen, China|date=2016-10-14|website=CleanTechnica|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref> The first public Skyrail line opened in [[Yinchuan]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chinaplus.cri.cn/news/china/9/20180110/76330.html|title=New unmanned SkyRail service unveiled in NW China|website=chinaplus.cri.cn|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chinaplus.cri.cn/news/china/9/20180110/76330.html|title=New unmanned SkyRail service unveiled in NW China|website=chinaplus.cri.cn|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref> A number of Chinese cities such as [[Guilin]], [[Shantou]], [[Guang'an Metro|Guang'an]], and [[Bengbu]] have ordered Skyrail lines in development.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cleantechnica.com/2017/09/12/byd-announces-first-commercial-skyrail-line-yinchuan-china/|title=BYD Announces 1st Commercial SkyRail Line In Yinchuan, China|date=2017-09-12|website=CleanTechnica|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref> By 2019, a number of cities around the world had placed orders for Skyrail systems.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201805/26/WS5b08dce6a31001b82571c729.html|title=BYD to increase market presence of SkyRail - Chinadaily.com.cn|last=\u674e\u677e|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metrocptm.com.br/chinesa-byd-pode-assumir-fabricacao-de-monotrilho-da-linha-17-ouro/|title=Chinesa BYD assumir\u00e1 fabrica\u00e7\u00e3o de monotrilho da Linha 17-Ouro|date=2018-12-21|website=Metr\u00f4 CPTM|language=pt-BR|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n\n===Mobile phone components===\n{{main|BYD Electronic}}\nMobile phone components were added to the BYD product line in the early 2000s. But this business, [[BYD Electronic]], was spun off in 2007.<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\">{{cite web|url=http://www.byd-electronic.com/abu/files/20080424/20080424043806_2187.PDF |title=BYD Electronic (International) Company Limited Annual Report 2007 |format=PDF |date= 2007|accessdate=12 October 2010|quote=\"BYD Electronic\"... was spun off from BYD Company Limited and listed on the Main Board of the Stock Exchange Hong Kong Limited on 20 December 2007. It is a world-leading vertically integrated provider of handset components and modules manufacturing as well as assembly services. The Company provides services to brand name vendors of handsets as original equipment manufacturers...}}</ref>\n\n==Corporate affairs==\nThe company has its corporate headquarters in the [[Pingshan New Area]] in [[Longgang District, Shenzhen|Longgang District]], [[Shenzhen]], [[Guangdong| Guangdong province]]. Its North American headquarters are in [[Downtown Los Angeles]], and BYD has sales offices in various countries.<ref>\"[http://bydit.com/doce/contact/ContactUs/index.html Contact Us] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222193031/http://bydit.com/doce/contact/ContactUs/index.html |date=22 February 2015 }}.\" BYD Company. Retrieved on 17 June 2015. \"BYD COMPANY LIMITED Headquarters Add.: No.3009, BYD Road, Pingshan, Shenzhen, 518118, P.R.China \" - [http://bydit.com/docc/contact/contact/index.html Chinese address]: \"\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8 \u603b\u90e8 \u5730\u5740\uff1a\u6df1\u5733\u5e02\u576a\u5c71\u65b0\u533a\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u8def3009\u53f7 \u90ae\u7f16\uff1a518118 \" - \"BYD North America Headquarters Add.:1800 S. Figueroa Street, Los Angeles, CA90015, USA\"</ref>\n\n==Innovation==\nThe company has been recognized for innovation; for example it has developed technologies that allow mobile phone batteries to be made at room temperature rather than in expensive, heated dry rooms.<ref name=economistinn>[http://www.economist.com/specialreports/displaystory.cfm?story_id=15879359First break all the rules: A special report on innovation in emerging markets; The charms of frugal innovation] economist.com, 15 April 2010</ref>\n\nIn 2010, BusinessWeek ranked BYD the eighth most innovative company in the world <ref name=businessweek>{{cite magazine|url=http://bwnt.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/innovative_companies_2010/ |title=The 50 Most Innovative Companies 2010 |magazine=[[BusinessWeek]] |accessdate=17 April 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100418203357/http://bwnt.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/innovative_companies_2010/ |archivedate=18 April 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> and that same year saw Fast Company ranking BYD as the 16th most innovative.<ref name=fastcompany>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/mic/2010 |title=The World's Most Innovative Companies 2010 |magazine=[[Fast Company (magazine)|Fast Company]] |accessdate=17 April 2010 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100419083851/http://www.fastcompany.com/mic/2010| archivedate= 19 April 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, PV Magazine has awarded BYD the top category of innovation on its newly launched battery storage system that advances progress in three categories: modularity, charging and discharging capacity, and efficiency. <ref>[https://www.currentgeneration.co.nz/solargridconnected/BYD+STRIDES+FORWARD+WITH+A+HIGH+VOLTAGE+BATTERY+STORAGE+SYSTEM.html BYD STRIDES FORWARD WITH A HIGH VOLTAGE BATTERY STORAGE SYSTEM, PV Magazine 2017-12-08 Retrieved 2018-05-25]</ref>\n\n==Subsidiaries==\nThe company has a number of subsidiaries, including [[BYD Auto]]. The following is an incomplete list.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\">{{cite web|url=http://www.byd-electronic.com/abu/files/20090421/20090421021430_1156.pdf |title=BYD Co Ltd 2008 Annual Report |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=12 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===BYD (H.K.) Co Ltd===\nTrading in NiCd, NiMH and Li-ion batteries and related products,<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/> it is a wholly owned subsidiary of '''BYD Co Ltd''' that in turn wholly owns Golden Link Worldwide Limited.<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\"/>\n*Golden Link Worldwide Ltd is an investment holding company [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] in the British Virgin Islands.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/> A wholly owned subsidiary of BYD (H.K.) Co Ltd,<ref name=\"reorg notice\">{{cite web|url=http://notice.singtao.com/ADMA/01211/epdf/BYD(9).pdf |title=Further Reorganisation of the Be Group for the Proposed Spin-Off And Adjournment of Egms in Respect of the Proposed Spin-Off |format=PDF |accessdate=12 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716074455/http://notice.singtao.com/ADMA/01211/epdf/BYD%289%29.pdf |archivedate=16 July 2011 }}</ref> itself a wholly owned subsidiary of BYD Co Ltd,<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\"/> as of 2007 Golden Link held nearly 70% issued share capital of [[BYD Electronic|BYD Electronic (International) Co Ltd]].<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\"/>\n\n===Shenzhen BYD Electronic Parts Co Ltd===\nProduction and sale of NiMH and NiCD batteries, hardware products, instruments and flexible\nprinted circuit boards are performed by this subsidiary.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===Shenzhen BYD Microelectronics Co Ltd===\nEstablished in 2002,<ref name=\"TM1\">[http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1928671/ BYD Acquires SinoMOS] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081015153430/http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1928671/ |date=15 October 2008 }} tradingmarkets.com Wed. 8 October 2008</ref> it is responsible for the design, production and sale of [[Integrated circuit|ICs]] for use in the mobile phone industry.<ref name=\"TM2\">[http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1928481/ BYD Said to Buy Wafer Assets]{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} tradingmarkets.com Wed. 8 October 2008</ref> It is registered as a sino-foreign joint venture.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===Shenzhen BYD Daimler New Technology Company===\n{{main|Denza}}\nA joint venture with German [[Daimler AG]], Denza focuses on producing electric vehicles that eschew the BYD brand name.\n\n===BYD Electronic Co Ltd===\nAn investment holding company [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] in the Cayman Islands.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===BYD Electronic Hungary Kft===\nOriginally Mirae Hungary Industrial Manufacturer Ltd, and responsible for the manufacture and sale of mobile handset components, BYD Electronic Hungary Kft was purchased from Mirae Industry Co Ltd on 12 February 2008.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/> Prior to the purchase, it manufactured handset housings for Nokia.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===Foshan Jinhui Hi-tech Optoelectronic Material Co Ltd===\nA joint venture with Foshan Plastic Group Co Ltd and BYD (H.K) Co Ltd,<ref name=\"Stub\">[http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1G1-143774465.html Foshan Plastic Group starts special cell production.(NEWSDESK: Cooperation)(Foshan Jinhui High-Tech Photoelectric Material Co. Ltd.)] China Chemical Reporter, 26 February 2006</ref> it manufactures material ion exchange membranes.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n==Production bases and facilities==\nBYD has many production bases, including three locations in [[Shenzhen]]<ref name=\"Brochure\">[http://www.byd.com/downloads/broucher/2.pdf BYD Co Ltd Company Brochure] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100215035322/http://www.byd.com/downloads/broucher/2.pdf |date=15 February 2010 }} BYD Auto Official Site</ref> (one of which is on the self-titled 'BYD Road' ({{zh|s=\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u8def|t=\u6bd4\u4e9e\u8fea\u8def|p=B\u01d0y\u00e0d\u00ed L\u00f9}}) in [[Pingshan New District]], [[Longgang District, Shenzhen]]),<ref name=\"Brochure\"/> as well as sites in [[Huizhou]],<ref name=\"Brochure\"/> [[Shanxi]],<ref name=\"BYD2\"/> and [[Shanghai]].<ref name=\"BYD2\"/>\n\nAuto production bases include an automobile assembly line in [[Xi'an]], a [[BYD electric bus|K9 electric bus]] manufacturing plant in [[Dalian]],<ref>{{cite web|title=\u6e2f\u5a92\uff1a\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u7eaf\u7535\u52a8\u5df4\u58eb\u5927\u8fde\u4e0b\u7ebf \u7535\u6c60\u9879\u76ee\u5df2\u6b63\u5f0f\u542f\u52a8|url=http://finance.ifeng.com/a/20141229/13391461_0.shtml |website=\u51e4\u51f0\u8d22\u7ecf|accessdate=29 December 2014|language=Chinese}}</ref> a photovoltaic module (solar panel) Bloomberg New Energy Finance Tier 1 manufacturing plant in [[Beijing]], an R&D center and nascent automobile assembly line in Shenzhen, and an R&D center in Shanghai.<ref name=\"BYD Auto About\"/>\n\nUS operations can be found in [[Elk Grove Village, Illinois]], and [[San Francisco]], California.<ref name=gunther/> BYD also acquired a site for a future North American headquarters in downtown [[Los Angeles]], and has built and operates a manufacturing plant in [[Lancaster, California]], near Los Angeles.<ref>For Illinois location, see {{cite web\n |url=http://blogdowntown.com/2010/04/5321-chinese-auto-maker-byd-locating-its-north \n |title=Chinese Auto Maker BYD Locating its North American Headquarters Downtown on Figueroa \n |publisher=[[blogdowntown]] \n |date=30 April 2010 \n |accessdate=1 May 2010 \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100504055949/http://blogdowntown.com/2010/04/5321-chinese-auto-maker-byd-locating-its-north \n |archivedate=4 May 2010 \n |url-status=live \n}}\n*For California location, see {{cite web\n |url=http://www.contracostatimes.com/california/ci_14986910 \n |title=Chinese auto, solar firm BYD chooses LA as its US headquarters \n |publisher=[[Contra Costa Times]] \n |date=30 April 2010 \n |accessdate=1 May 2010 \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100503153018/http://www.contracostatimes.com/california/ci_14986910 \n |archivedate=3 May 2010 \n |url-status=live \n}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 a bus plant opened in [[Newmarket, Ontario]] to handle orders in Canada.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.byd.com/news-posts/byd-opens-first-canadian-bus-assembly-plant/ |title=BYD Opens First Canadian Bus Assembly Plant|publisher=BYD North America|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBy 2020, BYD converted some of its equipment to produce 5 million [[N95 mask]]s per day to reduce the spread of [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Xie |first1=John |title=World Depends on China for Face Masks But Can Country Deliver? {{!}} Voice of America - English |url=https://www.voanews.com/science-health/coronavirus-outbreak/world-depends-china-face-masks-can-country-deliver |website=www.voanews.com |publisher=[[Voice of America]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200321094219/https://www.voanews.com/science-health/coronavirus-outbreak/world-depends-china-face-masks-can-country-deliver |archivedate=21 March 2020 |language=en |date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Legal disputes==\nBYD was unsuccessfully sued by [[Sony]] and [[Sanyo]] for patent infringement.<ref name=gunther/> The [[Taiwan|Taiwanese]] [[OEM]] [[Foxconn]] has also brought a suit against the company for the same reason.<ref name=chiu>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/innovationNews/idUSTRE48S19B20080929 |title=Buffett's BYD endorsement sends shares soaring |author=Joanne Chiu and Alison Leung |work=Reuters |date=29 September 2008 |accessdate=3 May 2009 }}</ref>\n\nIn addition to patent litigation, Foxconn has sued BYD in [[Hong Kong]] and [[Illinois]] court in 2007, alleging that BYD poached 50 Foxconn employees and was complicit in the stealing of trade secrets, in order to set up a competing cell phone manufacturing operation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/39099077/ns/business-us_business/t/look-inside-foxconn-where-iphones-are-made/|title=A look inside Foxconn - where iPhones are made: a postmodern Chinese industrial empire that was blighted by suicides|last=|first=|date=12 September 2010|website=|access-date=22 May 2019}}</ref> Court proceedings were brought before BYD Electronic was [[Spin-off (corporate)|spun off]] by BYD later in 2007, delaying the public listing<ref>{{cite web |title=Commercial espionage between Foxconn and BYD |url=http://ipr.chinadaily.com.cn/2012-12/25/content_16053023.htm |website=ipr.chinadaily.com.cn |accessdate=22 May 2019}}</ref> on the Hong Kong [[stock exchange]] by half a year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Move to metal casings for smartphones to benefit BYD Electronic, Ju Teng |url=https://www.scmp.com/business/china-business/article/1482794/move-metal-casings-smartphones-benefit-byd-electronic-ju |website=South China Morning Post |language=en |date=15 April 2014}}</ref> \n\nFoxconn also opened proceedings in the district where BYD is headquartered, at the [[Shenzhen]] Intermediate People\u2019s Court, which referred the case to the [[Supreme People\u2019s Court]], which in turn commissioned an appraisal by the Beijing JZSC Intellectual Property Forensic Center into files in BYD's possession which were alleged to belong to Foxconn. Eventually the Shenzhen court made the final judgment: BYD's files contained non-public information originating from Foxconn, which could bring economic benefits to the holders, thereby, BYD was found guilty of infringing Foxconn\u2019s trade secrets.<ref>{{cite web |title=Commercial espionage between Foxconn and BYD |url=http://ipr.chinadaily.com.cn/2012-12/25/content_16053023.htm |website=ipr.chinadaily.com.cn}}</ref>\n\nAfterwards, Foxconn withdrew the civil proceedings against BYD in mainland China, and sought [[criminal prosecution]] instead. On March 20th 2008, the former Executive Director and Vice President of BYD was arrested. Then on March 24th and 31st 2008 two former employees of Foxconn were arrested and sentenced to 1 year and 4 months, and 4 years in prison respectively.<ref>{{cite web |title=Commercial espionage between Foxconn and BYD |url=http://ipr.chinadaily.com.cn/2012-12/25/content_16053023.htm |website=ipr.chinadaily.com.cn}}</ref>\n\nBYD issued a [[counterclaim]] to Foxconn in Hong Kong court, alleging [[defamation]] and bribery of Chinese officials as well as intimidation on Foxconn's part.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/39099077/ns/business-us_business/t/look-inside-foxconn-where-iphones-are-made/|title=A look inside Foxconn - where iPhones are made: a postmodern Chinese industrial empire that was blighted by suicides|last=|first=|date=12 September 2010|website=|access-date=22 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n\n*In September 2008, [[MidAmerican Energy Holdings]], a [[subsidiary]] of [[Warren Buffett]]'s [[Berkshire Hathaway Inc.]], invested about US$230&nbsp;million for a 10% (or 9.89%<ref name=\"lipolymer-battery\">[https://www.lipolymer-battery.com lipolymer-battery] lipolymer-battery, 1 Apr 2020</ref>) share of BYD @ HK$8/share.<ref name=chiu/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[BYD Auto]]\n*[[BYD Electronic]]\n*[http://www.bydforklift.com/ BYD Forklift] \n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20161030140807/http://www.byd.com/usa/truck/ BYD Truck]\n*[[Lithium iron phosphate battery]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|BYD Company}}\n*[http://www.byd.com.cn/ BYD Company Limited]\n*[https://www.sec.gov/cgi-bin/browse-edgar?company=&match=&CIK=0001445162&Find=Find+Companies&action=getcompany SEC CIK# 0001445162 - ADR listing, etc.]\n{{Automotive industry in the People's Republic of China}}\n{{SZSE 100 Index}}\n{{FTSE China A50 Index}}\n{{Hang Seng China Enterprises Index}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Byd Company}}\n[[Category:BYD Company| ]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Companies in the CSI 100 Index]]\n[[Category:Vehicle manufacturing companies established in 1995]]\n[[Category:Chinese companies established in 1995]]\n[[Category:Electronics companies of China]]\n[[Category:Civilian-run enterprises of China]]\n[[Category:Berkshire Hathaway]]\n[[Category:H shares]]\n[[Category:Electric vehicle battery manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Battery manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies of China]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies headquartered in China]]\n[[Category:Chinese brands]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{for|its automaker subsidiary|BYD Auto}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = BYD Co Ltd <br /> \u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\n| logo = BuildYourDreams.svg\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{hkse|1211}}<br>{{szse|002594}}\n| genre = \n| foundation = {{start date and age|1995|2|df=yes}}\n| founder = [[Wang Chuanfu]]\n| location_city = [[Shenzhen]], [[Guangdong]]\n| location_country = China\n| location = \n| origins = \n| key_people = Wang Chuanfu ([[Chairman]], [[CEO]])\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| industry = [[Automobiles]], [[Buses]], [[Electric bicycle]], [[Truck]], [[Forklift]], [[Solar Panels]], [[Rechargeable batteries]]\n| products = Gasoline and electric cars, battery-powered bicycles, buses, truck, forklift, photovoltaic modules (solar panels), rechargeable batteries and handset components.\n| services = \n| revenue = US$8.5&nbsp;billion (2013)\n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| num_employees = 220,000 in 2017<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = [[BYD Automobile]]<br>[[BYD Electronic]]\n| owner = {{unbulleted list\n | [[Berkshire Hathaway]]<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-03-09|title=Why China's War on Pollution Affects the Whole World|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/graphics/2018-china-pollution/|newspaper=Bloomberg.com|via=www.bloomberg.com|quote=Beneficiaries include BYD Co., a Warren Buffett-backed carmaker that soared 67 percent last year and sold more cars than Tesla.}}</ref> (24.6%)<ref name=\"4-traders\">{{cite web|title=BYD Company|url=http://www.4-traders.com/BYD-COMPANY-LIMITED-5640763/company/|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref>\n | Xiang Yang L\u00fc (21.6%)<ref name=\"4-traders\"/>\n | [[Wang Chuanfu]] (15.7%)<ref name=\"4-traders\"/>\n}}\n| homepage = [http://www.byd.com www.byd.com]\n}}\n\n{{Chinese|s=\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8|t=|p=B\u01d0y\u00e0d\u00ed G\u01d4f\u0113n Y\u01d2uxi\u00e0n G\u014dngs\u012b|order=st}}\n'''BYD Co Ltd''' is a Chinese manufacturer of automobiles, battery-powered bicycles, buses, forklifts, solar panels, rechargeable batteries (varied inc. bulk-storage from renewable energy), trucks, etc.<ref name=\"BYD2\">[http://www.bydit.com/doce/about/company_p.asp Company Profile] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090427135652/http://www.bydit.com/doce/about/company_p.asp |date=27 April 2009 }} BYD Official Site</ref> with its corporate headquarters in [[Shenzhen]]. It has two major subsidiaries, [[BYD Automobile]] and [[BYD Electronic]]. It was founded in February 1995.\n\nBYD has grown to become a major manufacturer of automobiles, battery-powered bicycles, buses, truck, forklift, solar panels, rechargeable batteries, and most notably mobile-phone batteries.<ref name=gunther/>\n\nBYD topped the 2010 [[Bloomberg Businessweek]] Tech 100 list, a list of large, fast-growing tech companies.<ref name=businessweek2>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/it100_2010.html?chan=technology_special+report+--+tech+100_special+report+--+tech+100 |title=The Tech 100 |magazine=[[BusinessWeek]] |accessdate=26 May 2010 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100524080821/http://www.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/it100_2010.html?chan=technology_special+report+--+tech+100_special+report+--+tech+100| archivedate= 24 May 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n==Name==\nThe name BYD is an abbreviation of \"Build Your Dreams\".<ref name=\"NYT\">[https://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/13/business/worldbusiness/13chinacar.html?_r=1&ref=business A Small Showing, but With Big Dreams] NICK BUNKLEY\nPublished: 12 January 2009</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Byd us headquarter la.JPG|thumb|BYD US Headquarters in Los Angeles]]\nFounded in February 1995<ref name=\"BYD2\"/> and listed on the [[Hong Kong Stock Exchange]] on 31 July<ref name=\"BYD Auto About\">[http://www.byd.com/company.php?index=0 Company Profile] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090826100551/http://www.byd.com/company.php?index=0 |date=26 August 2009 }} BYD Auto Official Site</ref> 2002,<ref name=\"BYD1\">[http://www.byd.com.cn/Welcome to BYD]{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Company Introduction, BYD Official Site</ref> BYD Co Ltd began as a rechargeable-battery factory competing in the Chinese market against Japanese imports.<ref name=gunther/>\n\n===Early growth===\nBYD grew quickly within ten years capturing more than half the world's mobile-phone battery market<ref name=\"Book\"/> and becoming the largest Chinese manufacturer (and in the top four worldwide) of all types of [[rechargeable battery|rechargeable batteries]].<ref name=gunther>{{cite magazine|url=http://money.cnn.com/2009/04/13/technology/gunther_electric.fortune/ |title=Why Warren Buffett is investing in electric car company BYD |author=Marc Gunther |magazine=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] |date=13 April 2009 |accessdate=2 May 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090427114106/http://money.cnn.com/2009/04/13/technology/gunther_electric.fortune/ |archivedate=27 April 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Replacing work done by machines with cheap, local labor lowered costs,<ref name=\"Book\">[https://books.google.com/books?id=aKfmQdqvk0wC&pg=PA215&dq=BYD&client=safari#v=onepage&q=BYD&f=false China, Inc. By Ted Fishman] Google Books, page 215</ref> and the company began expanding beyond batteries adding automobiles and mobile phone components.\n\n===Automobiles===\n{{main|BYD Automobile}}\nA year after the 2002 acquisition of Tsinchuan Automobile Co Ltd, [[BYD Auto|BYD Automobile Co Ltd]] was born.<ref name=\"BYD Auto About\"/> One of many Chinese automakers, in 2010 it was the sixth largest in terms of sales volume.<ref>[http://www.thetruthaboutcars.com/2011/01/china-car-market-101-who-makes-all-those-18-million-cars/ China Car Market 101: Who Makes All Those 18 Million Cars?] thetruthaboutcars.com, 19 January 2011</ref>\n\nSeeking to utilize BYD battery production resources, it sells electric cars in addition to gasoline-powered models.\n\nIn late 2017, the premier of the government of [[Ontario]], Canada announced that BYD would open a factory in the province to manufacture electric vehicles. Other sources indicated that the plant could open as early as 2018.<ref> {{Cite web|url=https://canada.businesschief.com/marketing/2202/Chinas-BYD-to-open-electric-vehicle-plant-in-Ontario|title=China\u2019s BYD to open electric vehicle plant in Ontario|website=canada.businesschief.com|access-date=2019-05-31}}</ref> BYD already had a small Canadian office in Windsor, Ontario at the time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/queenspark/2017/12/01/chinese-truck-manufacturer-to-open-ontario-factory-premier-says-on-trade-trip.html|title=Chinese truck manufacturer to open Ontario factory, Premier says on trade trip {{!}} The Star|website=thestar.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Monorail Transit ===\nIn 2016, BYD unveiled a working monorail prototype known as \"Skyrail\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.byd.com/skyrail/|title=SKYRAIL|website=BYD USA|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.byd.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/SkyRail%20Brochure.pdf|title=BYD SkyRail|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> and announced they will enter the global rail transit market.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cleantechnica.com/2016/10/14/byd-unveils-skyrail-test-track-shenzhen-china/|title=BYD Unveils SkyRail Test Track In Shenzhen, China|date=2016-10-14|website=CleanTechnica|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref> The first public Skyrail line opened in [[Yinchuan]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chinaplus.cri.cn/news/china/9/20180110/76330.html|title=New unmanned SkyRail service unveiled in NW China|website=chinaplus.cri.cn|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chinaplus.cri.cn/news/china/9/20180110/76330.html|title=New unmanned SkyRail service unveiled in NW China|website=chinaplus.cri.cn|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref> A number of Chinese cities such as [[Guilin]], [[Shantou]], [[Guang'an Metro|Guang'an]], and [[Bengbu]] have ordered Skyrail lines in development.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cleantechnica.com/2017/09/12/byd-announces-first-commercial-skyrail-line-yinchuan-china/|title=BYD Announces 1st Commercial SkyRail Line In Yinchuan, China|date=2017-09-12|website=CleanTechnica|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref> By 2019, a number of cities around the world had placed orders for Skyrail systems.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201805/26/WS5b08dce6a31001b82571c729.html|title=BYD to increase market presence of SkyRail - Chinadaily.com.cn|last=\u674e\u677e|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metrocptm.com.br/chinesa-byd-pode-assumir-fabricacao-de-monotrilho-da-linha-17-ouro/|title=Chinesa BYD assumir\u00e1 fabrica\u00e7\u00e3o de monotrilho da Linha 17-Ouro|date=2018-12-21|website=Metr\u00f4 CPTM|language=pt-BR|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n\n===Mobile phone components===\n{{main|BYD Electronic}}\nMobile phone components were added to the BYD product line in the early 2000s. But this business, [[BYD Electronic]], was spun off in 2007.<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\">{{cite web|url=http://www.byd-electronic.com/abu/files/20080424/20080424043806_2187.PDF |title=BYD Electronic (International) Company Limited Annual Report 2007 |format=PDF |date= 2007|accessdate=12 October 2010|quote=\"BYD Electronic\"... was spun off from BYD Company Limited and listed on the Main Board of the Stock Exchange Hong Kong Limited on 20 December 2007. It is a world-leading vertically integrated provider of handset components and modules manufacturing as well as assembly services. The Company provides services to brand name vendors of handsets as original equipment manufacturers...}}</ref>\n\n==Corporate affairs==\nThe company has its corporate headquarters in the [[Pingshan New Area]] in [[Longgang District, Shenzhen|Longgang District]], [[Shenzhen]], [[Guangdong| Guangdong province]]. Its North American headquarters are in [[Downtown Los Angeles]], and BYD has sales offices in various countries.<ref>\"[http://bydit.com/doce/contact/ContactUs/index.html Contact Us] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222193031/http://bydit.com/doce/contact/ContactUs/index.html |date=22 February 2015 }}.\" BYD Company. Retrieved on 17 June 2015. \"BYD COMPANY LIMITED Headquarters Add.: No.3009, BYD Road, Pingshan, Shenzhen, 518118, P.R.China \" - [http://bydit.com/docc/contact/contact/index.html Chinese address]: \"\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u80a1\u4efd\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8 \u603b\u90e8 \u5730\u5740\uff1a\u6df1\u5733\u5e02\u576a\u5c71\u65b0\u533a\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u8def3009\u53f7 \u90ae\u7f16\uff1a518118 \" - \"BYD North America Headquarters Add.:1800 S. Figueroa Street, Los Angeles, CA90015, USA\"</ref>\n\n==Innovation==\nThe company has been recognized for innovation; for example it has developed technologies that allow mobile phone batteries to be made at room temperature rather than in expensive, heated dry rooms.<ref name=economistinn>[http://www.economist.com/specialreports/displaystory.cfm?story_id=15879359First break all the rules: A special report on innovation in emerging markets; The charms of frugal innovation] economist.com, 15 April 2010</ref>\n\nIn 2010, BusinessWeek ranked BYD the eighth most innovative company in the world <ref name=businessweek>{{cite magazine|url=http://bwnt.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/innovative_companies_2010/ |title=The 50 Most Innovative Companies 2010 |magazine=[[BusinessWeek]] |accessdate=17 April 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100418203357/http://bwnt.businessweek.com/interactive_reports/innovative_companies_2010/ |archivedate=18 April 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> and that same year saw Fast Company ranking BYD as the 16th most innovative.<ref name=fastcompany>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/mic/2010 |title=The World's Most Innovative Companies 2010 |magazine=[[Fast Company (magazine)|Fast Company]] |accessdate=17 April 2010 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100419083851/http://www.fastcompany.com/mic/2010| archivedate= 19 April 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, PV Magazine has awarded BYD the top category of innovation on its newly launched battery storage system that advances progress in three categories: modularity, charging and discharging capacity, and efficiency. <ref>[https://www.currentgeneration.co.nz/solargridconnected/BYD+STRIDES+FORWARD+WITH+A+HIGH+VOLTAGE+BATTERY+STORAGE+SYSTEM.html BYD STRIDES FORWARD WITH A HIGH VOLTAGE BATTERY STORAGE SYSTEM, PV Magazine 2017-12-08 Retrieved 2018-05-25]</ref>\n\n==Subsidiaries==\nThe company has a number of subsidiaries, including [[BYD Auto]]. The following is an incomplete list.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\">{{cite web|url=http://www.byd-electronic.com/abu/files/20090421/20090421021430_1156.pdf |title=BYD Co Ltd 2008 Annual Report |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=12 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===BYD (H.K.) Co Ltd===\nTrading in NiCd, NiMH and Li-ion batteries and related products,<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/> it is a wholly owned subsidiary of '''BYD Co Ltd''' that in turn wholly owns Golden Link Worldwide Limited.<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\"/>\n*Golden Link Worldwide Ltd is an investment holding company [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] in the British Virgin Islands.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/> A wholly owned subsidiary of BYD (H.K.) Co Ltd,<ref name=\"reorg notice\">{{cite web|url=http://notice.singtao.com/ADMA/01211/epdf/BYD(9).pdf |title=Further Reorganisation of the Be Group for the Proposed Spin-Off And Adjournment of Egms in Respect of the Proposed Spin-Off |format=PDF |accessdate=12 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716074455/http://notice.singtao.com/ADMA/01211/epdf/BYD%289%29.pdf |archivedate=16 July 2011 }}</ref> itself a wholly owned subsidiary of BYD Co Ltd,<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\"/> as of 2007 Golden Link held nearly 70% issued share capital of [[BYD Electronic|BYD Electronic (International) Co Ltd]].<ref name=\"BYD Electronic 2007 Report\"/>\n\n===Shenzhen BYD Electronic Parts Co Ltd===\nProduction and sale of NiMH and NiCD batteries, hardware products, instruments and flexible\nprinted circuit boards are performed by this subsidiary.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===Shenzhen BYD Microelectronics Co Ltd===\nEstablished in 2002,<ref name=\"TM1\">[http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1928671/ BYD Acquires SinoMOS] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081015153430/http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1928671/ |date=15 October 2008 }} tradingmarkets.com Wed. 8 October 2008</ref> it is responsible for the design, production and sale of [[Integrated circuit|ICs]] for use in the mobile phone industry.<ref name=\"TM2\">[http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1928481/ BYD Said to Buy Wafer Assets]{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} tradingmarkets.com Wed. 8 October 2008</ref> It is registered as a sino-foreign joint venture.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===Shenzhen BYD Daimler New Technology Company===\n{{main|Denza}}\nA joint venture with German [[Daimler AG]], Denza focuses on producing electric vehicles that eschew the BYD brand name.\n\n===BYD Electronic Co Ltd===\nAn investment holding company [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] in the Cayman Islands.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===BYD Electronic Hungary Kft===\nOriginally Mirae Hungary Industrial Manufacturer Ltd, and responsible for the manufacture and sale of mobile handset components, BYD Electronic Hungary Kft was purchased from Mirae Industry Co Ltd on 12 February 2008.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/> Prior to the purchase, it manufactured handset housings for Nokia.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n===Foshan Jinhui Hi-tech Optoelectronic Material Co Ltd===\nA joint venture with Foshan Plastic Group Co Ltd and BYD (H.K) Co Ltd,<ref name=\"Stub\">[http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1G1-143774465.html Foshan Plastic Group starts special cell production.(NEWSDESK: Cooperation)(Foshan Jinhui High-Tech Photoelectric Material Co. Ltd.)] China Chemical Reporter, 26 February 2006</ref> it manufactures material ion exchange membranes.<ref name=\"BYD 2008 Report\"/>\n\n==Production bases and facilities==\nBYD has many production bases, including three locations in [[Shenzhen]]<ref name=\"Brochure\">[http://www.byd.com/downloads/broucher/2.pdf BYD Co Ltd Company Brochure] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100215035322/http://www.byd.com/downloads/broucher/2.pdf |date=15 February 2010 }} BYD Auto Official Site</ref> (one of which is on the self-titled 'BYD Road' ({{zh|s=\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u8def|t=\u6bd4\u4e9e\u8fea\u8def|p=B\u01d0y\u00e0d\u00ed L\u00f9}}) in [[Pingshan New District]], [[Longgang District, Shenzhen]]),<ref name=\"Brochure\"/> as well as sites in [[Huizhou]],<ref name=\"Brochure\"/> [[Shanxi]],<ref name=\"BYD2\"/> and [[Shanghai]].<ref name=\"BYD2\"/>\n\nAuto production bases include an automobile assembly line in [[Xi'an]], a [[BYD electric bus|K9 electric bus]] manufacturing plant in [[Dalian]],<ref>{{cite web|title=\u6e2f\u5a92\uff1a\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8fea\u7eaf\u7535\u52a8\u5df4\u58eb\u5927\u8fde\u4e0b\u7ebf \u7535\u6c60\u9879\u76ee\u5df2\u6b63\u5f0f\u542f\u52a8|url=http://finance.ifeng.com/a/20141229/13391461_0.shtml |website=\u51e4\u51f0\u8d22\u7ecf|accessdate=29 December 2014|language=Chinese}}</ref> a photovoltaic module (solar panel) Bloomberg New Energy Finance Tier 1 manufacturing plant in [[Beijing]], an R&D center and nascent automobile assembly line in Shenzhen, and an R&D center in Shanghai.<ref name=\"BYD Auto About\"/>\n\nUS operations can be found in [[Elk Grove Village, Illinois]], and [[San Francisco]], California.<ref name=gunther/> BYD also acquired a site for a future North American headquarters in downtown [[Los Angeles]], and has built and operates a manufacturing plant in [[Lancaster, California]], near Los Angeles.<ref>For Illinois location, see {{cite web\n |url=http://blogdowntown.com/2010/04/5321-chinese-auto-maker-byd-locating-its-north \n |title=Chinese Auto Maker BYD Locating its North American Headquarters Downtown on Figueroa \n |publisher=[[blogdowntown]] \n |date=30 April 2010 \n |accessdate=1 May 2010 \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100504055949/http://blogdowntown.com/2010/04/5321-chinese-auto-maker-byd-locating-its-north \n |archivedate=4 May 2010 \n |url-status=live \n}}\n*For California location, see {{cite web\n |url=http://www.contracostatimes.com/california/ci_14986910 \n |title=Chinese auto, solar firm BYD chooses LA as its US headquarters \n |publisher=[[Contra Costa Times]] \n |date=30 April 2010 \n |accessdate=1 May 2010 \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100503153018/http://www.contracostatimes.com/california/ci_14986910 \n |archivedate=3 May 2010 \n |url-status=live \n}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 a bus plant opened in [[Newmarket, Ontario]] to handle orders in Canada.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.byd.com/news-posts/byd-opens-first-canadian-bus-assembly-plant/ |title=BYD Opens First Canadian Bus Assembly Plant|publisher=BYD North America|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBy 2020, BYD converted some of its equipment to produce 5 million [[N95 mask]]s per day to reduce the spread of [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Xie |first1=John |title=World Depends on China for Face Masks But Can Country Deliver? {{!}} Voice of America - English |url=https://www.voanews.com/science-health/coronavirus-outbreak/world-depends-china-face-masks-can-country-deliver |website=www.voanews.com |publisher=[[Voice of America]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200321094219/https://www.voanews.com/science-health/coronavirus-outbreak/world-depends-china-face-masks-can-country-deliver |archivedate=21 March 2020 |language=en |date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Legal disputes==\nBYD was unsuccessfully sued by [[Sony]] and [[Sanyo]] for patent infringement.<ref name=gunther/> The [[Taiwan|Taiwanese]] [[OEM]] [[Foxconn]] has also brought a suit against the company for the same reason.<ref name=chiu>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/innovationNews/idUSTRE48S19B20080929 |title=Buffett's BYD endorsement sends shares soaring |author=Joanne Chiu and Alison Leung |work=Reuters |date=29 September 2008 |accessdate=3 May 2009 }}</ref>\n\nIn addition to patent litigation, Foxconn has sued BYD in [[Hong Kong]] and [[Illinois]] court in 2007, alleging that BYD poached 50 Foxconn employees and was complicit in the stealing of trade secrets, in order to set up a competing cell phone manufacturing operation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/39099077/ns/business-us_business/t/look-inside-foxconn-where-iphones-are-made/|title=A look inside Foxconn - where iPhones are made: a postmodern Chinese industrial empire that was blighted by suicides|last=|first=|date=12 September 2010|website=|access-date=22 May 2019}}</ref> Court proceedings were brought before BYD Electronic was [[Spin-off (corporate)|spun off]] by BYD later in 2007, delaying the public listing<ref>{{cite web |title=Commercial espionage between Foxconn and BYD |url=http://ipr.chinadaily.com.cn/2012-12/25/content_16053023.htm |website=ipr.chinadaily.com.cn |accessdate=22 May 2019}}</ref> on the Hong Kong [[stock exchange]] by half a year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Move to metal casings for smartphones to benefit BYD Electronic, Ju Teng |url=https://www.scmp.com/business/china-business/article/1482794/move-metal-casings-smartphones-benefit-byd-electronic-ju |website=South China Morning Post |language=en |date=15 April 2014}}</ref> \n\nFoxconn also opened proceedings in the district where BYD is headquartered, at the [[Shenzhen]] Intermediate People\u2019s Court, which referred the case to the [[Supreme People\u2019s Court]], which in turn commissioned an appraisal by the Beijing JZSC Intellectual Property Forensic Center into files in BYD's possession which were alleged to belong to Foxconn. Eventually the Shenzhen court made the final judgment: BYD's files contained non-public information originating from Foxconn, which could bring economic benefits to the holders, thereby, BYD was found guilty of infringing Foxconn\u2019s trade secrets.<ref>{{cite web |title=Commercial espionage between Foxconn and BYD |url=http://ipr.chinadaily.com.cn/2012-12/25/content_16053023.htm |website=ipr.chinadaily.com.cn}}</ref>\n\nAfterwards, Foxconn withdrew the civil proceedings against BYD in mainland China, and sought [[criminal prosecution]] instead. On March 20th 2008, the former Executive Director and Vice President of BYD was arrested. Then on March 24th and 31st 2008 two former employees of Foxconn were arrested and sentenced to 1 year and 4 months, and 4 years in prison respectively.<ref>{{cite web |title=Commercial espionage between Foxconn and BYD |url=http://ipr.chinadaily.com.cn/2012-12/25/content_16053023.htm |website=ipr.chinadaily.com.cn}}</ref>\n\nBYD issued a [[counterclaim]] to Foxconn in Hong Kong court, alleging [[defamation]] and bribery of Chinese officials as well as intimidation on Foxconn's part.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/39099077/ns/business-us_business/t/look-inside-foxconn-where-iphones-are-made/|title=A look inside Foxconn - where iPhones are made: a postmodern Chinese industrial empire that was blighted by suicides|last=|first=|date=12 September 2010|website=|access-date=22 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==In the media==\n\n*In September 2008, [[MidAmerican Energy Holdings]], a [[subsidiary]] of [[Warren Buffett]]'s [[Berkshire Hathaway Inc.]], invested about US$230&nbsp;million for a 10% (or 9.89%<ref name=\"wedowebapps\">[https://www.wedowebapps.com mobile app development company]{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=wedowebapps|fix-attempted=yes }} wedowebapps, 21 Oct 2019</ref>) share of BYD @ HK$8/share.<ref name=chiu/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[BYD Auto]]\n*[[BYD Electronic]]\n*[http://www.bydforklift.com/ BYD Forklift] \n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20161030140807/http://www.byd.com/usa/truck/ BYD Truck]\n*[[Lithium iron phosphate battery]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|BYD Company}}\n*[http://www.byd.com.cn/ BYD Company Limited]\n*[https://www.sec.gov/cgi-bin/browse-edgar?company=&match=&CIK=0001445162&Find=Find+Companies&action=getcompany SEC CIK# 0001445162 - ADR listing, etc.]\n{{Automotive industry in the People's Republic of China}}\n{{SZSE 100 Index}}\n{{FTSE China A50 Index}}\n{{Hang Seng China Enterprises Index}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Byd Company}}\n[[Category:BYD Company| ]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Companies in the CSI 100 Index]]\n[[Category:Vehicle manufacturing companies established in 1995]]\n[[Category:Chinese companies established in 1995]]\n[[Category:Electronics companies of China]]\n[[Category:Civilian-run enterprises of China]]\n[[Category:Berkshire Hathaway]]\n[[Category:H shares]]\n[[Category:Electric vehicle battery manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Battery manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies of China]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies headquartered in China]]\n[[Category:Chinese brands]]\n", "name_user": "Lance sql", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(lipolymer-battery)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BYD_Company"}
